social_posts.post_text: Was quite a moment for me last weekend. Just started playing music again after close to 20 years cause I wanted to concentrate on a new career as an actor. It’s was a crossroads for me, and had to walk away. 30 years later my OG band @speculablack decided to record again ( thanks to vanhelsing showrunner @j_l_walker for being so kind to ask for one of our song for my final episode of VanHelsing. What a gift!) now we just released a bunch of songs on all platforms. THEN!!! This happened!!! My great friend @edwardquinn recorded a KILLER album and his team said  he has to do a video for #LightsOutLove, so he asked if I would join the band. I LOST MY SHIT!!!! Then Ed asked if I knew a drummer. Well, I know one of the best drummers in all of rock! @brentfitz!!! Who plays with #slash #ftmileskennedy and #theconspirators !!! Brent and I grew up together in the bar scene back in #winnipeg, and played a few times together. haven’t played next to each other for over 30 years. We have kept in touch over the years and I was so proud of him doing what he was meant to do all over the world in front of millions in of people!!! Never in my wildest dreams did I think I would have this moment with my buddy again! THANK YOU QUINNER!! And meeting @thegreataddo ( insane music mind) what a blast! Hit it off right away and rocked the fuck out!! What a dream this was! Best part? It ain’t over!! Stay tuned! #rock #metal #bass #friends #dreams #LuckyYeti

Born in Winnipeg, Aleks Paunovic knew from an early age that he was destined to tell stories; whether it was with his fists as an amateur boxing champion, with his instrument as a musician, or in the truest form of storytelling: acting.

Portraying a myriad of roles on both screens big and small, Aleks has brought forth his unique skill set and chameleon-like talent to transform himself into each character he plays. Whether it is a developmentally disabled man accused of murder in Personal Effects (opposite Kathy Bates, Ashton Kutcher, and Michelle Pfeiffer), or as an overzealous karate dad opposite Tom Hardy in This Means War, Aleks truly takes each role to a new level further conditioning and developing his craft.

For more information on Aleks and his roles and achievements: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0006820/?ref_=nm_mv_close @alekspaun

Aleks Paunovic will be in the Queen City for the 2023 Cincinnati Comic Expo!
Featured in over 100 projects, Aleks' credits include Stargate SG-1, Battlestar Galactica, Stargate: Atlantis, Smallville, Once Upon a Time, Percy Jackson: Sea of Monsters, Psych, iZombie, Continuum, Supernatural, War for the Planet of the Apes, The 100, and more! 
In just the last few years, Aleks has appeared on Arrow, in Cold Pursuit, The Sinners, Van Helsing, See, and NarcoLeap. Fans will also recognize him from Hawkeye on Disney+, Snowpiercer on TNT, FUBAR on Netflix, as well as the Zero Contact film series alongside Sir Anthony Hopkins and the television series, GenZeroes.

Get your admission tickets to the 2023 Cincinnati Comic Expo for an opportunity to get an autograph and photo all weekend long with@alekspaun in the link in the bio.

Had a blast working on the 2nd season of #mostDangerousGame with some immense talent. and some intense Russian. Posted @withregram • @xxenomorph69 Самая опасная игра (Most Dangerous Game: #NewYork) 2 сезон. Дата выхода 10.03.2023.

Второй сезон сконцентрируется на неудачливом бойце Викторе, готовом на все, чтобы защитить свою сестру. Когда она оказывается в беде, он бросается искать полмиллиона долларов, которые нужны для того, чтобы помочь ей. Виктор соглашается принять участие в смертельно опасной игре: в течение 24 часов за ним будут охотиться на улицах Нью-Йорка пять самых опытных охотников в мире. И если он выживет, то заработает целое состояние.

Моя оценка 8/10. Неплохой клишированный боевичок.
